				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is the bard epic still worth the effort?<a name="35069"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 16 04 3:22 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You could look at it as either a blessing or a curse, but yes..  The Bard Epic is very difficult to bag, it is so useful to us.
<br />

<br />
The Epic's one major downside is its DMG/DLY ratio.  You can get better in the Bazaar, not to mention all of the good weapons raiding Bards keep bagged with their Epic still glued to their offhand.
<br />

<br />
Dance of the Blades proc...  Only really replacable with a Songblade in Time.  Many Time-flagged Bards never get one because it is such a rare drop. /rude Inny
<br />

<br />
1.8 mod for all instruments...
<br />
- Brass is easy enough to replace with an LDoN aug.
<br />
- String you could use a Tear Shaped Ring if you were really lucky in HoH or happened to be able to afford one if it actually went for sale in the Bazaar.
<br />
- Percussion there is always the Battle-Drummer, but that's not really much of an upgrade over the Epic.  Better DMG/DLY ratio, but crappy stats.
<br />
- Wind is next to impossible short of a Coirnav kill or a Time Saryrn.
<br />
- Singing is next to impossible even for Elemental-flagged Bards, Hydrotha is a stingy POS..  Probably took lessons from Phinny.  The good news with Singing is there is a 1.6 mod Cloak dropping in Gates trials (got mine in trial 2).  Sure, that's not as good as the Epic but it's close enough for me considering the rarity of other Singing options.  Plus, you can easily boost it with a VoTS.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
